.TH "sh_early_platform_driver_probe" 9 "sh_early_platform_driver_probe" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sh_early_platform_driver_probe \- probe a class of registered drivers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" sh_early_platform_driver_probe
.BI "(char *class_str "  ","
.BI "int nr_probe "  ","
.BI "int user_only "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "class_str" 12
string to identify early platform driver class
.IP "nr_probe" 12
number of platform devices to successfully probe before exiting
.IP "user_only" 12
only probe user specified early platform devices
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Used by architecture code to probe registered early platform drivers
within a certain class. For probe to happen a registered early platform
device matching a registered early platform driver is needed.
